.TH _printf 3
.SH NAME
_printf


.SH SYNOPSIS

#include "main.h"
.br
int print_char(va_list args);
.br
int print_string(va_list args);
.br
int print_integer(va_list args);
.br
int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.br
int print_perc(va_list args);
.br
int _strlen(char *str);

.SH DESCRIPTION
Displays a string in the format with the following options

.SH Conversion specifiers

.TP
%i
Display an integer

.TP
%d
Displays an integer as %i

.TP
%c
Displays a character

.TP
%s
Displays a string

.TP
%%
Displays the % sign

.TP
%b
Convert and display an integer in binary form

The function analyzes the string passed as a parameter and replaces each specifier with the corresponding value provided through the variable argument list.

.SH EXEMPLE

_printf("Number %d", number_a);

.SH AUTHOR
Sarah Wacquiez & Christophe Saniez-Lenthieul

